!front: What is the algebraic definition the **Dot Product**?
!back:
Consider two vectors \( \mathbf{a} \) and \( \mathbf{b} \) in an \( n \)-dimensional space \( \mathbf{a} = \langle a_1, a_2, \ldots, a_n \rangle \), \( \mathbf{b} = \langle b_1, b_2, \ldots, b_n \rangle \).

The **Dot Product** of \( \mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{b} \) is computed as the sum of the products of the corresponding components:

\[ \mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{b} = a_1 b_1 + a_2 b_2 + \ldots + a_n b_n = \sum_{i = 1}^{n} a_i b_i \]
~~~

